what is arrays?
~ its a variable whre you can put multiple value. but in line

let array= [50,60,29,35]   // this is how you can declare array
array index count start with 0 than 1 than2

example:

let anime=[ 'Naruto','Bleach','One peice']         // declare array
console.log(anime)
output:
0.Naruto
1.Bleach
2.One peice

so you can see its start with 0 index
anime[2] = One peice                                //single array declare
so there is array name: anime
if you command anime.lenght it will show 3          //array leangth

^^ array are mutible, 
you can change array after declaration like;
anime[2] = "vinland saga"                            // change the arrays
the 2 no index is now change "One peice" to "vindland saga"


^^ Loops in arrays

^^ for loop                                           //for loop

for(let i = 0; i<anime.length; i++){                 // this is for loop syntex
    console.log(anime[i])
}

^^ for of loop                                        //for loop

for (big of anime){                                // its make anime name big 
    console.log(big)
}

^^important method for arrays...
1.anime.push("aot")                                //push method
this method push new item in array in last

